"title": "8610: prayer, as asking God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8610",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God wants his people to turn to him in prayer, individually and corporately, in times of need or crisis, and to bring requests to him as a Father.</p>\n<h2>God's people are commanded to bring their requests to him</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:6\">PHP 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:11\">1CH 16:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:7\">MAT 7:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:9\">LUK 11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:24\">JHN 16:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:18-Eph6:20\">EPH 6:18–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:17\">1TH 5:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:13\">JAS 5:13</a></p>\n<h2>Prayer for deliverance from difficulty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:1\">PSA 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:6\">PSA 107:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:2-Ps40:3\">PSA 40:2–40:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:1-Jonah2:3\">JON 2:1–2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:5\">ACT 12:5</a></p>\n<h2>Prayer for deliverance from enemies</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps17:8-Ps17:9\">PSA 17:8–17:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:4\">PSA 35:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:9-2Kgs19:11\">2KI 19:9–19:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:11\">2CH 14:11</a></p>\n<h2>Prayers of individuals in time of crisis</h2>\n<h3>Jacob's prayer</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:9-Gen32:12\">GEN 32:9–32:12</a></p>\n<h3>David's prayers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:1-Ps28:9\">PSA 28:1–28:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps4:1\">PSA 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:1-Ps5:3\">PSA 5:1–5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:8-Ps30:10\">PSA 30:8–30:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps142:1-Ps142:7\">PSA 142:1–142:7</a></p>\n<h3>Elijah's prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:4\">1KI 19:4</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jeremiah's prayer</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:15-Jer15:18\">JER 15:15–15:18</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's prayers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:35-Mark14:36\">MRK 14:35–14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42-Luke22:44\">LUK 22:42–22:44</a></p>\n<h2>Individual petition to God in prayer</h2>\n<h3>Individual prayer for guidance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:12-Gen24:14\">GEN 24:12–24:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:1-Judg1:2\">JDG 1:1–1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:36-Judg6:40\">JDG 6:36–6:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:41\">1SA 14:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:1\">2SA 2:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr14:14-1Chr14:15\">1CH 14:14–14:15</a></p>\n<h3>Individual prayer for healing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:1-2Kgs20:11\">2KI 20:1–20:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa38:1-Isa38:10\">ISA 38:1–38:10</a></p>\n<h3>Individual prayer for the birth of a child</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:10-1Sam1:11\">1SA 1:10–1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:21\">GEN 25:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:17\">GEN 30:17</a></p>\n<h2>Corporate petition to God</h2>\n<h3>Corporate prayer for deliverance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:23\">EXO 2:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:15-Num20:16\">NUM 20:15–20:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut26:6-Deut26:8\">DEU 26:6–26:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:9\">JDG 3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:3\">JDG 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:7-Judg6:10\">JDG 6:7–6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:8\">1SA 12:8</a></p>\n<h3>Corporate prayer for restoration</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:23-Ps44:26\">PSA 44:23–44:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:8-Ps79:9\">PSA 79:8–79:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:4-Ps80:7\">PSA 80:4–80:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps85:4-Ps85:7\">PSA 85:4–85:7</a></p>\n<h3>Corporate prayer for protection, especially at times of crisis</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:21-Ezra8:23\">EZR 8:21–8:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:12-2Chr20:13\">2CH 20:12–20:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:1\">EZR 10:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:16\">EST 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:18-Ps74:23\">PSA 74:18–74:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:17-Dan2:18\">DAN 2:17–2:18</a></p>\n<h2>The first Christians prayed together when they met</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:13-Acts1:14\">ACT 1:13–1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:42\">ACT 2:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46-Acts2:47\">ACT 2:46–2:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:13\">ACT 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:16\">ACT 16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:36\">ACT 20:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:5\">ACT 21:5</a></p>\n<h2>The first Christians prayed together at times of crisis or important decisions</h2>\n<h3>When threatened with punishment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:24-Acts4:31\">ACT 4:24–4:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:5\">ACT 12:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:12\">ACT 12:12</a></p>\n<h3>When Barnabas and Saul were sent off by the church at Antioch</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:3\">ACT 13:3</a></p>\n<h3>When Paul and Silas experienced persecution</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25\">ACT 16:25</a></p>\n<h2>Prayers for mercy and grace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps143:1\">PSA 143:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:16\">HEB 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:18-2Chr6:19\">2CH 6:18–6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:1-Ps130:2\">PSA 130:1–130:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:30-Matt20:31\">MAT 20:30–20:31</a></p>",
